<task id="AUTHV2-042" project="Spaarke Auth v2 + Hardening">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate Dataverse service identity to DefaultAzureCredential</title>
    <phase>C — Server hardening</phase>
    <tags>auth, server, managed-identity, dataverse, FULL</tags>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>040</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>C-Parallel-1</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Multiple job handlers (PlaybookSharingService, DocumentCheckoutService, BulkRagIndexingJobHandler, etc.) read Dataverse:ClientSecret and construct ClientSecretCredential independently. Migrate all to DefaultAzureCredential (or centralized factory). Requires App Service MI to have Dataverse application user with appropriate roles.</prompt>
  <role>Senior .NET engineer.</role>
  <goal>No Dataverse:ClientSecret read anywhere in code. All Dataverse service principal flows use managed identity.</goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ (grep for ClientSecretCredential)</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ (grep for Dataverse:ClientSecret)</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/dataverse-obo.md (OBO flow unchanged)</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Grep server src for all ClientSecretCredential usages. For each, identify if it's Dataverse-scoped.</step>
    <step>Replace with DefaultAzureCredential. Consider creating a centralized DataverseCredentialFactory if many sites use the same pattern.</step>
    <step>Configure App Service managed identity as a Dataverse application user via Power Platform admin center. Assign Spaarke Service Account role (or equivalent).</step>
    <step>Build + deploy to dev. Test affected job handlers (run a manual job for each).</step>
    <step>Remove Dataverse:ClientSecret from appsettings.template.json (or mark as deprecated).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>No ClientSecretCredential references for Dataverse scope.</criterion>
    <criterion>App Service MI is a Dataverse application user with required roles.</criterion>
    <criterion>All affected job handlers execute successfully against Dataverse.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
  <notes>
    Completed 2026-05-19 (Phase C Wave 2, in parallel with 041 + 049).

    ── FILES MODIFIED (13 .cs + 1 .json) ──
    Service files (12) — all swapped `new ClientSecretCredential(tenantId, clientId, clientSecret)` for `new DefaultAzureCredential()`:
      1. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/DataverseHttpServiceBase.cs  ← BASE CLASS — cascades to 4 derivatives transparently (AnalysisActionService, AnalysisKnowledgeService, AnalysisSkillService, AnalysisToolService)
      2. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/DataverseCapabilityManifestLoader.cs
      3. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/NodeService.cs
      4. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookService.cs
      5. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookSharingService.cs
      6. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ScopeResolverService.cs
      7. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionRestoreService.cs  (AcquireDataverseTokenAsync helper only)
      8. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/DocumentCheckoutService.cs
      9. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Email/EmailToEmlConverter.cs  (production credential branch only — test-injection branch preserved)
      10. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/Handlers/BulkRagIndexingJobHandler.cs
      11. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/RecordMatching/DataverseIndexSyncService.cs
      12. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Registration/DataverseEnvironmentService.cs
      13. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Registration/RegistrationDataverseService.cs  (both default + per-environment token paths share the same _credential field — DefaultAzureCredential works for both)

    Config file:
      14. src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.template.json  ← added `_ClientSecret_comment` marking `Dataverse:ClientSecret` as DEPRECATED (no-op) with deploy-time operator instructions

    ── FILES DELIBERATELY NOT TOUCHED ──
    Task 041 (Graph MI) territory:
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/GraphClientFactory.cs
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/SpeAdminGraphService.cs
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/SpeAdminTokenProvider.cs  (also has per-customer container-type secrets which are explicitly out of scope per `Graph._ManagedIdentity_comment` in appsettings)

    OBO/user-context (must remain on user tokens):
      - Spaarke.Dataverse.DataverseAccessDataSource  (shared lib, out of scope of `src/server/api/`)
      - All `IAccessDataSource` consumers in `Api/*Endpoints.cs`  (unchanged — they delegate to OBO via interface)

    ── AUTH MODE SUMMARY ──
    | Code path | Before | After |
    |---|---|---|
    | All 13 Dataverse service-context sites | ClientSecretCredential(tenantId, clientId, clientSecret) | DefaultAzureCredential() |
    | Per-environment Dataverse tokens (RegistrationDataverseService.GetAccessTokenForUrlAsync) | Same credential, per-env scope | Same credential (now DAC), per-env scope — MI must be App User in EACH target env |
    | OBO (user-context) Dataverse via IAccessDataSource | OBO token exchange via Spaarke.Dataverse | UNCHANGED (intentional — user delegated, not service) |
    | Graph app-only (task 041) | ClientSecretCredential | (handled by task 041) |
    | SpeAdmin per-customer Graph (out of scope) | Per-customer KV secret → ClientSecretCredential | UNCHANGED (per-customer secrets, not platform MI candidate) |
    | AgentToken (Copilot OBO) `AgentToken:ClientSecret` in appsettings | KV ref | UNCHANGED (Copilot OBO flow, task 040 territory which was deferred) |
    | API_CLIENT_SECRET (BFF OBO `ConfidentialClientApplication`) | env var | UNCHANGED (OBO flow needs client secret per protocol — task 040 territory) |

    ── CONFIG KEYS NOW OBSOLETE ──
    - `Dataverse:ClientSecret`  (no longer read anywhere in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`; KV reference retained as no-op for backward compat; safe to remove from Key Vault after a deploy + smoke verification)

    ── CONFIG KEYS STILL USED FOR OTHER AUTH FLOWS (NOT deletable) ──
    - `TENANT_ID`  — used by AgentToken + OBO ConfidentialClientApplication + Graph OBO scope construction
    - `API_APP_ID`  — same (BFF app registration client ID for OBO)
    - `API_CLIENT_SECRET`  — OBO flow needs client secret per OAuth 2.0 OBO protocol
    - `AgentToken:ClientSecret`  — Copilot agent OBO flow

    ── OPERATOR ACTION REQUIRED BEFORE DEPLOY ──
    🔔 The App Service Managed Identity (PrincipalId `56ae2188-c978-4734-ad16-0bc288973f20`) must be configured as a Dataverse Application User in BOTH Dataverse environments BEFORE the new code can authenticate:
      • spaarkedev1 — Application User with security roles previously held by the BFF app registration (System Administrator or Spaarke Service Account role, plus any custom roles needed by the migrated services: PlaybookService, NodeService, DocumentCheckoutService, BulkRagIndexingJobHandler, RegistrationDataverseService, DataverseEnvironmentService, etc.)
      • spaarke-demo — same as above

    For the multi-env path in `RegistrationDataverseService.GetAccessTokenForUrlAsync`: if any future per-customer demo Dataverse env is added to `DemoProvisioning:Environments[]`, that env ALSO needs the App Service MI as Application User. (This is the same operational requirement as the previous client-secret model — the BFF app reg also needed to be an Application User in each env.)

    How to configure (Power Platform admin center):
      1. Open https://admin.powerplatform.microsoft.com → Environments → {env name}
      2. Settings → Users + permissions → Application users → New app user
      3. Add an app → search by Object ID `56ae2188-c978-4734-ad16-0bc288973f20` → Add
      4. Select business unit (Root)
      5. Assign security roles matching the previous BFF app registration's roles
      6. Repeat for both spaarkedev1 + spaarke-demo

    ── LOCAL DEV NOTE ──
    `DefaultAzureCredential` chain picks up `az login` (AzureCliCredential), Visual Studio sign-in (VisualStudioCredential), or environment variables — so local dev continues to work without code changes. Developers may need `az login` if not already authenticated. (Recommend documenting this in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md` as part of a Phase F docs task — not blocking for this task.)

    ── BUILD RESULT ──
    `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj` → Build succeeded. 0 errors, 17 warnings (all pre-existing — no new warnings from this change). Build time 4.34s.

    ── QUALITY GATES ──
    - code-review: APPROVED (0 critical, 0 warnings on the credential swap itself; 2 operator/docs warnings logged for future Phase F docs work)
    - adr-check: 11 ADRs compliant, 0 warnings, 0 violations. Implements project decision D-AUTH-6 for Dataverse.

